<div id="review_37576886" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/37576886" />
    <a title="Alexa Hamilton" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/165593-alexa-hamilton"><img alt="Alexa Hamilton" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1201493141p2/165593.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/37576886?book_show_action=true">Nov 12, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Alexa Hamilton" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Alexa Hamilton" href="/user/show/165593-alexa-hamilton">Alexa Hamilton</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer37576886" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4922519178869826162">Unbelievably good. I never thought I&apos;d say that about a book that incorporates Columbine, prison, drug addiction, Hurricane Katrina and troubled youth but it&apos;s the truth. I had to stop and sit and think after I finished this long book. After thinking for awhile, I realized that I would always think of Caelum Quirk, the main character and narrator, as a good friend even if he doesn&apos;t actually exist.</span>
  <span id="freeText4922519178869826162" style="display:none">Unbelievably good. I never thought I'd say that about a book that incorporates Columbine, prison, drug addiction, Hurricane Katrina and troubled youth but it's the truth. I had to stop and sit and think after I finished this long book. After thinking for awhile, I realized that I would always think of Caelum Quirk, the main character and narrator, as a good friend even if he doesn't actually exist.</span>
