<div id="review_27146788" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/27146788" />
    <a title="Denise" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1321103-denise"><img alt="Denise" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1224816602p2/1321103.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/27146788?book_show_action=true">Jul 13, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Denise" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Denise" href="/user/show/1321103-denise">Denise</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">anyone who loves Wally Lamb</span></div>

        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1321103-denise?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1321103-denise?shelf=knocked-my-socks-off">knocked-my-socks-off</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer27146788" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15521570869250859574">While I can understand why the reviews of this novel range from hot to cold, I loved it. I can not think of the last time I read a novel that contained so many current events and issues, all under the same cover.<br/><br/>I thought Lamb took a huge risk by weaving fictional characters in with the Columbine tragedy, but it worked. Not many authors could combine the two with such sensitivity. I thought his character development absolutely perfect.<br/><br/>I do admit that some of the thesis was a bit long and tedious</span>
  <span id="freeText15521570869250859574" style="display:none">While I can understand why the reviews of this novel range from hot to cold, I loved it. I can not think of the last time I read a novel that contained so many current events and issues, all under the same cover.<br /><br />I thought Lamb took a huge risk by weaving fictional characters in with the Columbine tragedy, but it worked. Not many authors could combine the two with such sensitivity. I thought his character development absolutely perfect.<br /><br />I do admit that some of the thesis was a bit long and tedious. But that did not prevent me from giving the novel 5 stars. </span>
  <a data-text-id="15521570869250859574" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

